Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
specifyCellPad(25.10)                                    specifyCellPad(25.10)

Name
       specifyCellPad  -  Specifies  leaf  cells  to  which padding (placement
       clearance) is to be added in the left, right, top, or bottom directions
       and a factor to use to calculate the padding dimension

Syntax
       specifyCellPad

       <leaf_cellName>

       {<padding> | [[-right <padding>]  [-left  <padding>]  [-top  <padding>]
       [-bottom <padding>]]}

       Specifies  leaf  cells  to which padding (placement clearance) is to be
       added in the left, right, top, or bottom directions and a factor to use
       to calculate the padding dimension. The placer adds the padding on  the
       sides  of the specified cells during placement. The padding is retained
       during optimization and CTS.

       If there are congestion problems,  delete  the  padding  by  using  the
       deleteAllCellPad command.

Parameters
       -bottom <bottomP> <adding>
              Specifies  a  factor  to  calculate the padding dimension on the
              bottom side.

              Minimum: 0

              Max: 500

       <leaf_cellName>
              Specifies the cell name(s) of a cell type to  which  the  factor
              applies. You can use wildcards (*) with this parameter.

       -left <leftPadding>
              Specifies  a  factor  to  calculate the padding dimension on the
              left side.

       <padding>
              Specifies a factor to use to calculate  the  padding  dimension.
              The placer multiplies the placement SITE by the factor. It reads
              the  placement  SITE  value from the technology file. The factor
              should be integer number only.

              The unit of padding on left/right side is the number  of  sites.
              The unit of padding on top/bottom side is the number of rows

       -right <rightPadding>
              Specifies  a  factor  to  calculate the padding dimension on the
              right side.

       -top <topPadding>
              Specifies a factor to calculate the padding dimension on the top
              side.

              Minimum: 0

              Max: 500

Example
       The following command adds padding that is twice the placement SITE  to
       leaf cells named FJK2:

       specifyCellPad FJK2 2

